text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!TypologyOfPhoneticContrasts]]%0a%0a!Presence of Uncommon Consonants: English and Hausa %0a%0a:Author: Thomas_H_K%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aLack of uncommon consonants in Hausa vs the [θ] found in English%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aSome consonants are only rarely employed in languages. These are referred to as the 'Uncommon Consonants:' clicks, labial-velars, 'th', and pharyngeals.%0a%0aClicks make a self-explanatory noise by expanding an air pocket trapped between the mouth and tongue until it releases, causing a noise. Commonly used for communication, but only rarely a linguistic feature.%0a%0aLabial-Velar involve the combination of two different plosive noises (ie [g͡b]) by pressing the tongue to tongue places while releasing the plsoive noise, thereby generating them simultaneously.%0a%0aPhyrangeals are produced when moving the root of the tongue so far back it occupies or stops the pharynx (which is the space above the larynx) during production.%0a%0a'Th' sounds are fricatives made by placing the tongue against the top teeth and softening the airstream (as opossed to a [s] which lets the airstream hit the teeth).%0a%0aEnglish only employs the 'th' sound out of these, whereas Hausa does not employ any. Note that Hausa is adjacent in the world to many languages with labial velars.%0a%0aInterestingly, while 'Th'and Phyrangeals originate from around the world, Labial-velars and Clicks are found almost exclusively in West and South Africa. Why did certain uncommon consonants develop in isolated areas only as opposed to others which developed concurrently in many families?%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: :)%0a(:Category: TypologyOfPhoneticContrasts:)
